race.comment: TIKEMYSON (1) goes on top. He's right up in the weights having carried 54kg when second in the Horsham Cup last time out but comes a fair way back in grade to a BM70 here and rising back out to 2400m from a good draw here should suit nicely. AUTUMNHEAT (2) was poor at Sandown Hillside last time when unable to make inroads from back in the field. Two wins in a row prior to that were good and he can bounce back. LEONCHROI (11) had too much to do off a slow speed at Seymour but flashed home late over 2000m to grab second. Ready for this trip now and will be hard to hold out. WAYED IN LIGHT (14) has upside off a dominant maiden win at Geelong and must be respected.
